[normal]are
[normal] removed.  Sponsorship by a Member of Parliament or 
[normal]members o
[normal]f a
[normal] Legislative Assembly should not, in my view, be a requirement
[normal] 
[normal]in
[normal] bringing a complaint to an 
[normal]omb
[normal]u
[normal]dsman
[normal].  The 
[normal]‘
[normal]twin-track approach
[normal]’
[normal] as proposed by the Law Commission for 
[normal]England
[normal] and 
[normal]Wales
[normal] would ensure that the citizen who wishes to complain has, if he or she so chooses, the support of their MP or MLA in bringing a complaint to an 
[normal]o
[normal]mbudsman
[normal].  This 
[normal]would also help maintain that vital link between the legislature and 
[normal]the
[normal] 
[normal]Ombudsman
